body:
Using a third-party processor that is from a company that is also an `upper body appendage`, so cannot provide you a code drop.

Version: Verilator 5.006 2023-01-22 rev v5.006 on Ubuntu-22.04

When verilating a particular portion of the verilog - I get the following errors:

```
%Error: Internal Error: <upper body appendage file>.vline:loc: ../V3Gate.cpp:1004: Can't replace lvalue assignments with const var
```

I originally added -fno-gate, but have been seeing some weird things that are going on in the simulation output vcd files, so decided to fix this and see if those resolve.

*Note:* Would be nice to allow the -fno-gate to be applied to only a single file of a larger design.

I tracked it down to the following style of code - and the driver of the wire - names of variables/wires have been changed.

```verilog
wire [4:0] foo;
// ... lots of other code.

`ifdef VERILATOR_WORKAROUND
  wire [4:1] foo_order;
  assign foo_order[1] = foo[0];
  assign foo_order[2] = |foo[1:0];
  assign foo_order[3] = |foo[2:0];
  assign foo_order[4] = |foo[3:0];

  assign foo[0] = a_bar_status[1];
  assign foo[1] = b_bar_status[1] & ~foo_order[1];
  assign foo[2] = c_bar_status[1] & ~foo_order[2];
  assign foo[3] = d_bar_status[1] & ~foo_order[3];
  assign foo[4] = e_bar_status[1] & ~foo_order[4];
`else
  assign foo[0] = a_bar_status[1];
  assign foo[1] = b_bar_status[1] & ~foo[0];
  assign foo[2] = c_bar_status[1] & ~(|foo[1:0]);
  assign foo[3] = d_bar_status[1] & ~(|foo[2:0]);
  assign foo[4] = e_bar_status[1] & ~(|foo[3:0]);
`endif
```

Since the above with `-DVERILATOR_WORKAROUND=1` works and there are no other internal errors, I'm no longer investigating this issue, but I thought I'd add it here so that you can augment your test suite to include this style and possibly fix it in the future.
